                "On the 2nd of July, 1980, fraters Aion and Shade spent the day at the Brooklyn Museum and the adjacent Botanical Gardens, viewing ancient artifacts and exotic plant life. Returning to Shade's home, they prepared for a ritual designed to earth the 11 titles of Maat upon the sephiroth as delineated by Soror Nema (see the Tree of Maat at the end of this site). After banishing by spacemarks, Shade invoked Thoth with his own words, and Aion called upon the Kia and the Zos with verses by A. O. Spare & Rehctaw invocation. They then read Liber Israfel sub figura LXIV in unison, and charged the temple by reading alternate chapters of Liber DCCCXIII vel ARARITA sub figura DLXX. Various sacraments were consumed, then each sphere's appropriate name was intoned as a mantra. Each then channelled a response in art, one in image and one in words. This continued through most of the night, until complete. Crowley's expression of Maat from The Vision & the Voice was read in unison. The spacemarks were repeated, and the temple was closed. This Work is the results of that working. It is interesting to note that no overt communication occured during the working other than the rite, thus the number of syncronicities between the sigils and the words was taken as some sort of proof. This working took place in the context of an extremely active period for the Horus/Maat Lodge, and was performed one week after the Warrior Lord Working at Nema's Maat Pangrove Abbey in Ohio, held at the summer solstice. This was a major gathering of magicians from around the country, notable for some of the earliest initiations done by the Lodge, and for a letter from Kenneth Grant which began the wider communication with the entity known as Lam, originally contacted by Aleister Crowley.",
